In March 2011, the school was criticized after an officer it employed used a [[taser]] to subdue a student in his room as he packed to leave following expulsion for use of [[marijuana]].<ref name=taser>[http://www.chattanoogan.com/articles/article_197465.asp Francis, Robert. ''Opinion. Should The Taser Be The First Response? - And Response.'' The Chattanoogan.] March 25, 2011. Accessed  2011-04-29.</ref> The school responded by noting the student refused to listen to instructions from the officer.<ref name=taser /> -->

==Academics==
The student-faculty ratio at Southern Adventist University is 16:1 and its most selected majors are [[biology|biological]] and [[biomedical]] sciences; business, management, marketing, and related support services; education; and health professions and related clinical sciences.<ref name="USNews"/> Southern offers 81 undergraduate degrees, with sixty majors, thirty-eight minors and two one-year certificate programs. It also offers master's degrees in business, [[Master of Education|education]], psychology, [[Master of Science in Nursing|nursing]], religion and [[Master of Social Work|social work]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Majors at Southern Adventist University|url=https://www.southern.edu/enrollment/academics/Pages/academics.aspx|publisher=Southern Adventist University|accessdate=2011-04-21}}</ref> The university is accredited by the [[Commission on Colleges of the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools]]<ref>{{Cite web 
|url=http://sacscoc.org/details.asp?instid=65700
|title=Southern Association of Colleges and Schools Commission on Colleges
|publisher=Commission on Colleges
|accessdate=2011-11-08
}}</ref> and the [[Adventist Accrediting Association|Accrediting Association of Seventh-day Adventist Schools, Colleges, and Universities]].<ref>{{Cite web
|url=http://education.gc.adventist.org/documents/accreditationstatus.pdf
|title=Post-Secondary Institutions Accreditation Status
|publisher=Seventh-day Adventist Church
|accessdate=2011-11-08
}}</ref>   In 2009, the ''[[Princeton Review]]'', an education services company, selected Southern as one of 141 institutions it listed in its "Best in the Southeast" section.<ref name=sptm08-07-02/><ref name="wdef2009">{{Citation 
|url=http://www.newschannel9.com/articles/southeast-983178-adventist-southern.html
|title=Southern Adventist University Named ''A Best in The Southeast'' College 
|work=News Channel 9
|publisher=Freedom Communications
|publication-date=2009-07-28
|accessdate=2011-06-05
}}</ref>

