Southern has more than {{convert|10|mi|km}} of hiking/mountain biking trails used by students and local community members alike.<!-- <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.southern.edu/enrollment/campuslife/Pages/recreation.aspx |title=Recreation |publisher=Southern Adventist University |date= |accessdate=2011-09-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtbtn.org/?p=882 |title=Two New Mountain Bike Trails Open in Chattanooga |publisher=Tennessee Mountain Biking Alliance |date=2011-04-19 |accessdate=2011-09-11}}</ref> --><ref>{{cite news|last=Miller |first=Rebecca |url=http://community.timesfreepress.com/news/2011/jul/06/new-road-trails-complete-collegedale/ |title=New off-road trails complete in Collegedale | newspaper=Weekly Community News |publisher=Chattanooga Times Free Press |date=2011-07-06 |accessdate=2011-09-11}}</ref><!-- <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rrca.org/programs/races/id/5095/ |title=Southern 6 Trail Race|publisher=Road Runners Club of America |date=2011-02-20 |accessdate=2011-09-11}}</ref> --> 

There is a campus-wide internet network with all classrooms accessing the wireless network and a computer lab in each building with access to printing. Wireless printing is also accessible in the dormitories.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collegeprowler.com/southern-adventist-university/#ixzz1ODRhb1cG |title=Southern Adventist University |publisher=College Prowler |date= |accessdate=2011-09-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.princetonreview.com/SouthernAdventistUniversity.aspx |title=Southern Adventist University |publisher=''The Princeton Review'' |date= |accessdate=2011-11-09}}</ref>

===Dormitories===
Southern's dormitories are [[Sex segregation|single gender]] although students can opt out of the dormitories during summer sessions or with permission from a dean. Upperclass and married students can receive exemptions from this policy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.southern.edu/enrollment/campuslife/Pages/studenthousing.aspx |title=Student Housing |publisher=Southern Adventist University |date= |accessdate=2011-09-11}}</ref>
The men's dormitory is Talge Hall and the women's dormitory is Thatcher Hall.<ref>{{cite web
| title = Member Services: Card Services
| url = http://www.collegedale.org/services_card.htm#ATM
| publisher = Collegedale Credit Union
| dateformat =
| accessdate = 2011-11-09}}
</ref> An accidental fire in Thatcher Hall in April 2005 killed one student and injured two others.<ref>[http://www.chattanoogan.com/articles/article_65999.asp "Fire Ruled Accidental In Which Southern Adventist Student Died"], ''[[The Chattanoogan]]'', April 26, 2005. Retrieved 2011-11-09.</ref> The dormitories have also been used to shelter storm victims who needed short-term housing, such as after tornadoes in early 2011.<ref>{{cite press release
|last= Haight
|first= Terry
| url=http://www.communityservices.org/article.php?id=185
| title=Disaster Response Report from GA-Cumberland Conference - May 5, 2011
| publisher=Adventist Community Services 
| accessdate=2011-11-09
| quote=in the US as of midnight Saturday, April 3}}</ref>

===WSMC-FM radio station===
{{main|WSMC-FM}}
Southern owns and operates FM radio station WSMC which is almost completely staffed by students and the only classical music station in the Chattanooga area. In 2003, following technical problems that caused the station to keep dropping off the air, WSMC upgraded equipment to improve its reliability.<ref>{{cite news | first = Rob | last = York | title = Upgrades Give Collegedale Radio Station Cleaner Sound | date = 7 February 2003 | url = http://www.chattanoogan.com/articles/article_32270.asp | work = [[The Chattanoogan]] | accessdate = 2011-05-31}}</ref> It has been in operation since 1961 and is located on campus.<ref name="simms">{{Citation 
|last=Simms
|first=Richard
|url=http://www.newschannel9.com/news/wsmc-2514-kornblum-years.html
|title=WSMC Selects New development Director
|work=News Channel 9
|publisher=Freedom Communications
|publication-date=2005-11-02
|accessdate=2011-11-09
}}</ref>

